 for bestpractices and # Dashboard

## Overview
Detailed, actionable development prompt for building a Studio Dashboard that summarizes active projects, recent decisions, pending client approvals, and quick actions. The prompt covers end-to-end requirements across frontend, backend, and integration, aligned to a responsive, mobile-first architecture with a polished design system. It includes all connected pages and features described in PROJECT CONTEXT, and prescribes data models, API contracts, UI components, and acceptance criteria to enable an AI development tool to generate working code and assets.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
The Dashboard page is the Studio landing screen shown after login. Its goals are to give users a high-level, at-a-glance status of ongoing work, recent decision activity, and immediate actions to keep projects moving. It should be highly scannable, customizable, and responsive for mobile and desktop.

Key aspects:
- Global chrome: Top navigation bar with a global search field, notifications bell, and user avatar/menu; a collapsible left sidebar for primary navigation; consistent white content surface with ample whitespace.
- Content zones:
  - Metrics Snapshot: Cards showing counts and small metrics such as pending approvals, active projects, average response time, and export credits remaining.
  - Projects List: A grid or list of Project Cards with status, last activity, and a pending approvals badge; actions per project (Open, Share, Archive).
  - Recent Activity Feed: Timeline-like feed showing approvals, comments, and exports with timestamps, user avatars, and quick context.
  - Quick Actions: Prominent, easily tappable actions such as Create Project, Create Decision, Upload Drawing, and Import Template. Each action launches a modal or inline form.
  - Notifications Summary: Inline pane summarizing recent approvals or reminders relevant to the user; link to full Notifications Center.
  - Search & Filter Bar: Prominent search with multi-facet filters for projects, decisions, templates, and files; filters for status, date range, team member, client, and priority.
- Visual alignment: Adhere to the Visual Style guidelines, ensuring high contrast typography, clear hierarchy, and consistent card-based organization.
- Connected features: This page integrates with Responsive Navigation, Notifications (Email & In-App), Search & Filter, User Authentication (SSO/Email), and Lightweight Tasks tied to Approvals.
- Data flows: Fetch live data from project service, decision service, and notification service; reflect in metrics, project cards, activity feed, and quick actions. Support client approvals state transitions (e.g., from decision outcomes to tasks) and instant UI feedback.

## Components to Build
- DashboardShell
  - Layout: 12-column responsive grid; left collapsible sidebar; topbar with global search, bell, avatar.
  - Responsiveness: Mobile-first, collapsible navigation, reflow to single-column on small screens.
- MetricsSnapshotCard
  - Props: metricLabel, value, delta, statusColor.
  - Visual: Small KPI tiles with icons and status badges.
- ProjectCard
  - Props: projectId, name, status, lastActivity, pendingApprovals, owner, colorAccent.
  - UI: Title, status badge, last activity text, pending approvals pill, action menu (Open, Share, Archive).
- RecentActivityFeed
  - Type: list of activity items with actor avatar, timestamp, action, and target (decision, comment, export).
- QuickActionsPanel
  - Actions: Create Project, Create Decision, Upload Drawing, Import Template.
  - Triggers: Modals or inline forms with required fields.
- SearchBarWithFilters
  - Features: Global search input with icon; multi-facet filters (status, owner, date range, project type, templates, files).
- NotificationsInlineCard (or Section)
  - Summary of latest reminders/approvals; a link to Notifications Center.
- Notifications Center Link/Shortcut
  - Quick navigation to the Notifications Center view.
- DataTableOrCardList
  - For projects: either grid of cards or compact list with sortable headers if used; supports infinite scroll or pagination as needed.
- EmptyStateComponents
  - For empty projects or no results in filters, with guided actions.
- ModalTemplates
  - Create Project modal, Create Decision modal, Upload Drawing modal, and any confirmation dialogs.

Technical details:
- UI kit integration: Use the UI Kit & Design System (see asset section) to ensure consistent typography, buttons, cards, and layout tokens.
- Visual states: Hover, focus, active, disabled; accessible focus rings; sufficient contrast per color tokens.
- Accessibility: Semantics (ARIA roles), keyboard navigable elements, screen reader friendly labels.

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Pages:
  - Dashboard (Studio Dashboard)
  - Reusable subcomponents as described above
- Components:
  - AppShell with responsive Sidebar and Topbar
  - KPI/Grid Card components
  - Project Card with status badge and actions
  - Activity Feed item components
  - Quick Actions panel with action triggers and modals
  - Search & Filter bar wired to global state
  - Notification inline widget and link to full Notifications Center
- Interactions:
  - Collapsible sidebar with animated transitions
  - Global search filters that reflect in project list and activity feed
  - Quick actions open modals or inline forms with validations
  - Live updates of metrics upon data fetch or simulated real-time updates
- State management:
  - Use a consistent state layer (e.g., React context or Redux) to share dashboard filters, list data, and user preferences
- API consumption (mock or real):
  - Fetch endpoints for:
    - GET /projects?filters...
    - GET /activities?... 
    - GET /metrics/dashboard
  - WebSocket or SSE for live activity if available (optional; provide fallback polling)
- Styling:
  - Implement according to Visual Style and Design System tokens
  - 12-column grid with 24–32px gutters
  - Cards with subtle shadows, clean borders, hover/tap affordances
- Accessibility:
  - Focus indicators, aria-labels, keyboard navigability
  - Color contrast checks

### Backend
- Endpoints (conceptual; implementable by your stack):
  - GET /dashboard/metrics
    - Returns: { pendingApprovals: int, activeProjects: int, avgResponseTimeMs: int, exportCredits: int }
  - GET /dashboard/projects
    - Query: page, pageSize, sort, filters (status, owner, dateRange, search)
    - Returns: [{ id, name, status, lastActivity, pendingApprovals, owner, colorAccent }, ...]
  - GET /dashboard/activities
    - Returns: [{ id, actorId, actorName, avatarUrl, action, targetType, targetId, timestamp }, ...]
  - POST /projects (for Create Project)
  - POST /decisions (for Create Decision)
  - POST /drawings/upload (for Upload Drawing)
  - POST /tasks (for lightweight tasks tied to approvals)
- Data models (simplified):
  - User: id, name, email, avatarUrl, roles, twoFactorEnabled
  - Project: id, name, status, ownerId, lastActivityAt, pendingApprovalsCount, colorAccent
  - Decision: id, projectId, title, options[], finalApprovalStatus, createdAt
  - Activity: id, actorId, action, targetType, targetId, timestamp
  - Task: id, title, assigneeId, relatedDecisionId, status, dueDate
- Security:
  - Ensure endpoints are protected by authentication; authorize based on user roles (studio user, admin)
- Validation:
  - Server-side validation for required fields; return meaningful error messages
- Data persistence:
  - Use existing project database or mock adapters; ensure idempotent reads; support pagination

### Integration
- Frontend-Backend communication:
  - REST API endpoints for metrics, projects, activities
  - WebSocket/SSE optional for live activity feed; default to periodic polling if not available
- State synchronization:
  - When a user performs a Quick Action (e.g., Create Decision), update central dashboard state and trigger a refresh of relevant sections
- Design system alignment:
  - All components consume the design tokens (colors, typography, spacing) from the UI Kit
- Notifications sync:
  - In-app notifications should reflect the same data as Email notifications; provide a link to notification settings

## User Experience Flow
1. User logs in and lands on Dashboard
2. Dashboard loads with:
   - KPI metrics updated
   - A grid/list of active projects with quick status badges
   - Recent activity feed showing recent approvals/comments/exports
   - Quick Actions visible for immediate project creation or decision entry
   - Search bar with filter options to narrow projects or decisions
3. User taps a Project Card to view details in Project Workspace
4. User uses Quick Actions to create a new project/decision or to upload a drawing
5. User interacts with the topbar notifications bell to view or mark as read; or navigates to Notifications Center
6. User accesses Admin Dashboard or User Profile via sidebar
7. If email verification is pending, the Email Verification Page is shown via the verification link
8. On mobile, the sidebar collapses; user uses topbar search and actions; dashboard components adapt to single-column stacking

## Technical Specifications

Data Models: Schema details
- User
  - id: string
  - email: string
  - name: string
  - avatarUrl: string
  - roles: string[]
  - twoFactorEnabled: boolean
  - connectedApps: string[] // for SSO or OAuth
- Project
  - id: string
  - name: string
  - status: string // e.g., "Active", "On Hold", "Completed"
  - ownerId: string
  - lastActivityAt: timestamp
  - pendingApprovals: number
  - colorAccent: string // hex
- Decision
  - id: string
  - projectId: string
  - title: string
  - options: Array<{ id: string, label: string, selected: boolean }>
  - finalApprovalStatus: string // "Approved", "Rejected", "Pending"
  - createdAt: timestamp
- Activity
  - id: string
  - actorId: string
  - action: string // "approved", "commented", "exported"
  - targetType: string // "Decision", "Comment", "Export"
  - targetId: string
  - timestamp: timestamp
- Task
  - id: string
  - title: string
  - assigneeId: string
  - relatedDecisionId: string
  - status: string // "Open", "InProgress", "Done"
  - dueDate: timestamp

API Endpoints: Routes and methods
- GET /dashboard/metrics
- GET /dashboard/projects
- GET /dashboard/activities
- POST /projects
- POST /decisions
- POST /drawings/upload
- POST /tasks
- GET /notifications (for Notifications Center)
- GET /users/me
- POST /auth/signup
- POST /auth/login
- POST /auth/refresh
- GET /verify-email?token=...

Security: Authentication, authorization requirements
- JWT-based authentication; access tokens with proper scopes
- Role-based access control: studioUser, admin (enterprise), client roles
- CSRF protection for state-changing operations
- Input sanitization and rate limiting for endpoints exposing actions (create, upload)

Validation: Input validation rules
- Required fields on project creation: name, ownerId
- Decision creation: projectId, title, options (non-empty)
- Upload drawing: file size limit, accepted mime types
- Sign-up: email format, password strength (min length, complexity), captcha optional
- 2FA setup toggles validated on server

Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Dashboard loads within 1.5s on standard network; metrics reflect current data
- [ ] Projects grid shows correct count and pending approvals badges
- [ ] Recent Activity Feed populates with latest three items and supports infinite scroll/pagination
- [ ] Quick Actions open modals with validated forms; successful submissions create records and refresh dashboard state
- [ ] Global search filters across projects, decisions, templates, and files; at least 90% match relevance
- [ ] Responsive behavior: layout gracefully stacks on mobile widths; all interactive elements remain tappable
- [ ] Notifications bell shows unread count; Notifications Center lists recent items; mark-as-read works
- [ ] Email Verification Page confirms activation and redirects to Dashboard
- [ ] Security: API endpoints require authentication; unauthorized access returns 401/403
- [ ] Data integrity: Created/updated records persist and are reflected across dashboard components

UI/UX Guidelines
Apply the project's design system:
- Follow the UI Kit tokens for color, typography, spacing
- Use Card-based layouts with clear hierarchy
